# Flycast Speech-to-Text

**API:** `window.SpeechRecognition` or `window.webkitSpeechRecognition`
- Continuous: `false` (stops after one utterance)
- Interim results: `true` (show text as it's being spoken)

**Language switcher:** English (en-US) default, Croatian (hr-HR). Set `recognition.lang` before starting.

**UI states:**
- Idle: microphone icon (outline)
- Listening: pulsing microphone icon (filled), visual feedback
- Error: show toast if unsupported

**Fallback:** If browser doesn't support Web Speech API, hide dictate button. Tooltip: "Speech-to-text requires a Chromium-based browser (Chrome, Edge, Opera)."

**Flow:** Transcribed text fills input; user can edit before sending.
